An Act relating to college sports; enacting the
Oklahoma College Athletic Conference Act; providing
legislative intent; defining terms; establishing the
Oklahoma NCAA Division II Athletic Conference
Exploration Commission; providing for membership;
providing for chairperson; requiring certain analysis
to be conducted by Commission; directing Commission
to consult with certain stakeholders; requiring
submission of feasibility report that includes
specific information; authorizing Commission to hire
independent consultants and contract with certain
experts; authorizing Commission to engage with the
NCAA; requiring submission of final report; creating
the Oklahoma NCAA Division II Athletic Conference
Exploration Commission Revolving Fund; authorizing
certain expenditures; requiring Commission to explore
certain funding sources; providing for codification;
and declaring an emergency.
SUBJECT: College sports
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 9101 of Title 70, unless there
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma
College Athletic Conference Act".

SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 9102 of Title 70, unless there
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
The purpose of this legislation is to establish a new
intercollegiate athletic conference, with name to be determined, to
promote and regulate college athletics among member institutions
within the state. This conference will provide enhanced athletic
competition, foster community and state pride, support student-
athlete experience by giving more time in classroom and creating
higher graduation rates, reduction of university athletic budgets
due to less travel, provide better in-state rivalries to enhance
student and spectator experience, allow better in-state recruiting
thus keeping Oklahoma students in Oklahoma, and ensure compliance
with both state and federal regulations governing college athletics.
SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 9103 of Title 70, unless there
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
As used in the Oklahoma College Athletic Conference Act:
1. "Commission" means the body established under this act to
explore the creation of a new NCAA Division II athletic conference
in this state;
2. "NCAA" means the National Collegiate Athletic Association;
3. "NCAA Division II" means the governing body for
intercollegiate athletics for NCAA-member institutions that compete
at the Division II level, which balances athletics, academics, and
extracurricular activities;
4. "Member institutions" means accredited colleges and
universities that would be potential members of the new NCAA
Division II conference;
5. "Student-athletes" means individuals enrolled in member
institutions who participate in NCAA Division II athletics; and
6. "The conference" means a collective body of NCAA Division II
institutions that would form an organized athletic conference under
the NCAA's rules and regulations.
